<title>SRI LANKA: Sri Lanka Jan-June tourist arrivals up 20.5 pct.</title>
<headline>Sri Lanka Jan-June tourist arrivals up 20.5 pct.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-08-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Tourist arrivals in Sri Lanka in the first six months of 1997 rose 20.5 percent to 174,200 from the year-earlier period, the Central Bank said on Monday.</p>
<p>Tourist arrivals in the first six months of 1996 were 144,600, it said.</p>
<p>Sri Lanka's tourism industry was badly hit last year, with arrivals down 25 percent, after rebel Tamil Tiger attacks on civilian targets.</p>
<p>The government expects more than 400,000 tourists this year.</p>
</text>
